caption: (Translated by Google) It is usually delicious with a light tonkotsu.  (Original) さっぱりしたとんこつで普通においしい。
The karamiso ramen is sooooo good, we have to order one more. This place is underrated.
We got the Shoyu Ramen and Gyoza set, with extra egg and spring onion. Bomb Ramen.

I went to this restaurant with my family during vacation. The food was ok but the service was absolute trash! The boss of the restaurant charged us $114 for a bowl of ramen. We noticed this and immediately told him. Instead of changing it he started arguing with us saying that we had made a mistake! He was very rude towards us and started pointing at us. He even added a 15 percent bill without telling us. In the end, he changed the bill and we walked away. I do not recommend this restaurant because of the terrible service provided to customers!

This shop automatically charges a 15% tip . The service was trash. When we first walked in the boss was having a full on argument with the table beside us. We waited for nearly 10 minutes for the waiters to pour us water and give us our menus. The ramen had a very hard texture. Meat tasted not fresh at all. We got and bill and found out that the boss charged us $150 for a bowl of ramen. The waiters apoligized for the mistake but the boss didn't give in. He started shouting and using his finger to point at us. We walked away and he was still shouting.

(Translated by Google) I have no choice but to give a tip, but it is basically unkind that the tip is included and calculated without anything I decide. In the small shop, other family guests don't have to call to calculate, so they can go and calculate it. This place was slammed when we walked up and the two servers were running around working their tails off. If they stopped to breathe for a second, they were still scanning the room looking for what was next.  The food was also delicious. My only complaint is their check in process was lackluster - they kind of ignore you until a table frees up, and there's no sign in sheet to establish an order so you can stand out of the way. I saw a bunch of people walk away that might not have if there had been a little more organization.
The staff there was friendly and patient but the ramen was so so.

We ordered a fried rice and a ramen set.  If you have ever eaten Costco instant ramen, yes, the ramen was exactly the same, same texture, same thickness... I’ve never seen this kind of ramen  in a ramen restaurant. It was surprisingly bad. The rice with the Karaage, which is the side of the ramen, was good. Asahi super dry was good too.  The fried rice was very dry — hard to swallow, with extra fat tonkatsu dice.  It was far below the average level of any kind of Hawaiien or Asian fried rice.  15% tip is automatically added to the bill, with a unfilled tip space on the receipt.
Better noodles and better broth than Bario next door. And less queues. Enough said
This ramen place serves the 'volcano ramen' which is interesting. However the noodle quality is average and the soup is a bit salty.

Really good ramen and service. We will return. We ordered the beef Kazan, spicy ramen and fried chicken. They were all good. The waiter service was also great. Our water was filled without having to find the sever. The spicy ramen was not too sweet spicy where your mouth becomes numb so that was good. Place was clean and the food came quickly.
(Translated by Google) Kazanramen on the second floor of the Royal Hawaiian Center is a pork bone ramen, but it is very delicious!  (Original) ロイヤルハワイアンセンターの2階にあるkazanramenは豚骨ラーメンですが、とても美味しいです！
Me and the son loved the spicy ramen
Delicious! Fast service and fair prices.
Ok ramen
This place has such a unique atmosphere. The Tantanmen was amazing!! I look forward to visiting again soon.

(Translated by Google) I got a volcano ramen. The noodles were dead in the soup. It is soft and soft, where is Koshi? The soup bowl for add-on is also replaced with a beaker for coffee, and the atmosphere of the ramen shop is ruined. Furthermore, the soup, which is the root of the taste, was precipitated in the supplementation, and the supplementation soup felt like just hot water. The number of staff members was very low at 8:00 pm, which was busy in Hawaii, and the floor was running alone, and the service was delayed. As a general, unfortunately, taste × service × price ×  (Original) 火山ラーメンを頂きました。スープの中で麺が死んでいました。ぬめぬめとし、柔らかい、コシはどこへ？継ぎ足し用のスープ容れ物もコーヒー用ビーカーで代用したようなもので、ラーメン店の雰囲気が台無しです。さらに、継ぎ足し用の中に味の根本である出汁が沈殿しており、継ぎ足しスープがただのお湯のように感じました。スタッフの人数も、ハワイで賑わう夜8時にしては非常に少なくフロアを一人で回しており、サービスも遅れが出ていました。総評として、残念ながら味×サービス×値段×
Great experience. Wonderful people, tasty food. Large ramen is enough for 2!
(Translated by Google) Never go. No taste, no serving, no mess. What service is received and 15% tip is forcibly collected?  (Original) 절대 가지마세요 맛도 없고 서빙도 엉망이고 무슨 서비스를 받았다고 15%팁을 강제 징수(?)하는지.....

I should've checked the review before blindly eating here. First of all they automatically charge 15% service charge for mediocre service.  Anyway, I ordered the spicy dry noodles and it was more SWEET than spicy. Disgusting.
Bland broth. 80% of my volcano sukiyaki ramen was bean sprouts. The beef was tough.  Would not recommend this place at all.
Bad service, had to wait 25min for ramen even no other customers were to serve. This is not Japanese ramen at all, avoid this.
(Translated by Google) The fried chicken is kept for a long time, the barbecue is full of fat, and the 15% tip is imposed.  (Original) 炸鸡像是放了很久的，叉烧全是肥的，强行加15%小费
Not the best I've had in Waikiki, still pretty good.
Disgusting

All ramen is chicken (tori) based broth. Prices are reasonable for Waikiki standards although there are many better ramen places. It’s a “pop up” so they may not be around for long. I had the poke donburi, no onions, for $5.98. It was okay. 15% service charge already added to the bill. They have lunch specials that look reasonable.
The food was really quite good, but overpriced for Ramen and the service was terrible.

They are located in the furtherest corner of Yokkocho. Food was just alright. Volcano ramen was very cool and filling but wasn’t authentic ramen noodles or soup. Price is ok compared since all the shops in Yokkocho is pretty expensive. 10% Kama’aina discount.

It is not traditional Japanese ramen. Soup is tasteless and salty. But volcano ramen is pretty cool, other than that taste is not good. Plus food is pretty pricey. and they charge 18% service fee mandatory.

(Translated by Google) Evaluation is a matter of taste preference. We ordered salt ramen. Narrow noodles thick. Because it includes service fee, no need for chips, both staff are crazy about smaho. Ramen shop next door is recommended.  (Original) 評価は味の好みの問題です。塩ラーメンをオーダー。細麺こってり。サービス料込みなのでチップは不要、店員は２人ともスマホに夢中。隣のラーメン屋のほうがオススメ。

I’ve eaten a lot of ramen in my life, this was one of the more memorable bowls! I got the tantan ramen which was super tasty and so filling! I would come again for sure.

(Translated by Google) Soy sauce ramen order, where are you making noodles? No pig bones! Tax inclusive of service tips $ 16 is expensive! No value!  (Original) 醤油ラーメン注文、麺はどこ製?不味い! 豚骨のこくもなし！税込サービスチップ込みで＄16は高い！価値なし!

Lunch special starts at $9.80! Super yummy Shio and Shoyu ramen. Staff is very friendly and prices are fair even at dinner. Can pay cash or card!
Be hungry !
One word.. YUMMMMMMMMMMM!!!!! The menu at this place is awesome. I only regret not eating there more.

While their normal ramen is mediocre, their specialty volcano ramen is terrible.  The stone bowl causes the noodles to burn and stick next to it.  The ramen itself is mostly vegetables and the meet mountain that they advertised for one of their dishes is meat wrapped around vegetables.  Not to mention there exceeding high prices.  Don’t go to this place,there are much better options in the gourmet alley.

(Translated by Google) The price of ramen is high ... but the same applies to all shops. If you want to eat gutsuri, Tonkotsu Volcano Ramen is recommended. The taste wasn't bad.  (Original) ラーメンの値段しては高い...がどのお店も同じこと。ガッツリ食べたいならばとんこつ火山ラーメンはおすすめです。味は悪くなかった。
Expensive
Great ramen

(Translated by Google) Since the place is a place, it is quite crowded. This is also natural, but it is time consuming, expensive and not delicious. I was convinced because I wanted to eat ramen for the time being. However, it will be about 1,500 yen in Japanese yen.  (Original) 場所が場所なので結構混んでます。これも当然なのですが時間がかかってかつ高くて美味しくない。取り敢えずラーメンが食べたかったので納得しました。但し、日本円で1,500円程度します。

Ordered the Shouyu tonkotsu. The noodle was well firm and reasonable thickness. But soup is missing something for tonkotsu. Japanese tonkotsu soup is much more than that taste. They need to put more efforts on the soup. Staffs were not friendly nor motivated.
Had noodles are Bario and enjoyed it. I found the regular to be more than enough. Very filling.

Ok ramen, I tasted better. The service was super slow even though there was only one other person in the restaurant. They forgot to give us water and the people who came in after us was given water instead and we had to ask them. The workers here like to ignore you too.
Ramen is so-so not comparable to Japan at all. Service is super slow and this is the most expensive ramen I've ever had! $28 for the ramen and 15% tip automatically included. Won't recommend at all.
Great food...friendly servers...the broth for the ramen is amazing!!
This isn't the best ramen in Waikiki, but it is darn close to it. I love the spicy tonkatsu and if I lived in Waikiki, I'd eat here at least once a week.
Some of the best ramen I've ever had. I got the chashu ramen miso with a soft boiled egg and it was absolutely amazing, I hope I get another chance to eat here again before I leave Hawaii

(Translated by Google) Order soy sauce ramen and salt ramen It is expensive at 13 $ each, but the taste is not good. I left ramen for the first time. The cup noodle felt better. Gyoza was delicious. After all Japanese ramen is the best!  (Original) 醤油ラーメンと塩ラーメンを注文 ひとつ13$とお高いですが、味はイマイチ。 初めてラーメンを残してしまいました。 カップヌードルの方がおいしく感じた。 餃子はおいしかったです。 やっぱり日本のラーメンが一番ですね！
So delicious! You can't miss it! Best ramen ever!
Love this place. Great food, came back 3 times.
The best ramen I have ever had. Everything was delicious
We stoped by to have cold Ramen that was advertised but no cold ramen was served. They advertised this as a main attraction but not available

Newly opened authentic Japanese Ramen joint. Still working out the kinks so service might be slow and food might ran out early.  But the soup stock and the noodles were unique enough to be worth the wait.  Ordered the Kazan (Volcano) Shouyu Ramen with menma (bamboo shoots, and yes that's her nickname, if it seemed familiar).  And got the green tea ice cream (matcha anmitsu) to go.
